The government will provide food and other humanitarian needs to more than 5,000 families affected by banditry in Kerio Valley and parts of Baringo.The families are located in Elgeyo Marakwet, Baringo, Turkana, Samburu and West Pokot counties.Rift Valley regional coordinator Wanyama Musiambo said they will be assisted to enable them to return to their normal lives following the agony they have gone through at the hands of armed bandits in the last 10 months.&ldquo;We have records of all those affected and none will be left out,&rdquo; he said.The families will also receive free fertiliser and seeds and help in ploughing 2,500 acres under a new programme to help rehabilitate them, Musiambo said.The programme will help to deal with food insecurity in the region, he added.Some Sh100 million will be used to compensate families of those who lost their lives or were injured in the attacks, and those whose property was destroyed.